ternational Master\u2019s Scholarships<\/span><\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<p><img fetchpriority=\"high\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-1831\" src=\"https:\/\/abroadin.com\/blog\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/07\/distance-learning-online-education-webpage-1.jpg\" alt=\"masters scholarships for international students\" width=\"750\" height=\"438\" srcset=\"https:\/\/abroadin.com\/blog\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/07\/distance-learning-online-education-webpage-1.jpg 750w, https:\/\/abroadin.com\/blog\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/07\/distance-learning-online-education-webpage-1-300x175.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 750px) 100vw, 750px\" \/><\/p>\n<h2><span style=\"color: #333333;\">1. Rhodes Scholarships<\/span><\/h2>\n<ul>\n<li><span style=\"color: #333333;\">Study in the UK<\/span><\/li>\n<li><span style=\"color: #333333;\">Masters\/Ph.D. Degree<\/span><\/li>\n<li><span style=\"color: #333333;\"><a style=\"color: #333333;\" href=\"https:\/\/www.rhodeshouse.ox.ac.uk\/scholarships\/the-rhodes-scholarship\/\">Official Scholarship Website<\/a><\/span><\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<p><span style=\"color: #333333;\">The Rhodes Scholarships are prestigious postgraduate awards that support exceptional students at the University of Oxford.<\/span><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"color: #333333;\">This program, created in 1902 by Cecil Rhodes, is recognized as the oldest and most esteemed international scholarship program. To apply for these masters scholarships for international students:<\/span><\/p>\n<ul>\n<li><span style=\"color: #333333;\">Applicants must meet the citizenship and residency requirements of the specific Rhodes constituency they are applying for.<\/span><\/li>\n<li><span style=\"color: #333333;\">They must be 18 to 24 on October 1st, 2023. Alternatively, for older candidates who completed their first undergraduate degree later than usual, they must be under the age of 27 on October 1st, 2023.<\/span><\/li>\n<li><span style=\"color: #333333;\">To be eligible for a full-time course at the University of Oxford, applicants should have completed an undergraduate degree with a First Class Honors Degree or equivalent.<\/span><\/li>\n<li><span style=\"color: #333333;\">Additionally, applicants must meet the English language proficiency requirements of the University of Oxford at the Higher Level listed.<\/span><\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<p>If you&#8217;re willing to study abroad, check this out \ud83d\udc47\ud83c\udffc<\/p>\n<p><strong><a class=\"raven-post-title-link\" href=\"https:\/\/abroadin.com\/blog\/student-exchange-programs-free\/\">All about Student Exchange Programs + 10 Free Exchange Programs<\/a><\/strong><\/p>\n<p>&nbsp;<\/p>\n<h2><span style=\"color: #333333;\">2. The University of Twente Scholarships<\/span><\/h2>\n<ul>\n<li><span style=\"color: #333333;\">Study in the Netherlands<\/span><\/li>\n<li><span style=\"color: #333333;\">Master\u2019s Degree<\/span><\/li>\n<li><span style=\"color: #333333;\"><a style=\"color: #333333;\" href=\"https:\/\/www.utwente.nl\/en\/education\/scholarship-finder\/university-of-twente-scholarship\/\">Official Scholarship Website<\/a><\/span><\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<p><span style=\"color: #333333;\">Suppose you are an excellent student from an EU\/EEA or non-EU\/EEA country planning to pursue a graduate program (MSc) at the University of Twente.<\/span><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"color: #333333;\">In that case, you may be eligible for University Twente Scholarships (UTS). To qualify for these masters scholarships for international students, you need to meet the following requirements:<\/span><\/p>\n<ul>\n<li><span style=\"color: #333333;\">Apply for a UT scholarship separately from your course entry application to the University of Twente.<\/span><\/li>\n<li><span style=\"color: #333333;\">Obtain an admission letter from the university, regardless of funding.<\/span><\/li>\n<li><span style=\"color: #333333;\">Be admitted to one of the qualifying UT Master programs that start in September 2023\/2024. It may take up to eight weeks to receive results after completing your application.<\/span><\/li>\n<li><span style=\"color: #333333;\">Have a student number.<\/span><\/li>\n<li><span style=\"color: #333333;\">Not have graduated from a UT graduate program.<\/span><\/li>\n<li><span style=\"color: #333333;\">To obtain an entry visa for the Netherlands meet the requirements. It includes achieving a minimum score of 6.5 on the Academic IELTS (or 90 on the TOEFL iBT) and a minimum of 6.0 on the speaking sub score of the test.<\/span><\/li>\n<li><span style=\"color: #333333;\">Not eligible for a Dutch study loan.<\/span><\/li>\n<li><span style=\"color: #333333;\">Belong to the top 5 to 10 percent of your class, as the University Twente Scholarship is reserved for excellent students.<\/span><\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<p>&nbsp;<\/p>\n<h2><span style=\"color: #333333;\">3. Italian Government Scholarships for Foreign Students<\/span><\/h2>\n<ul>\n<li><span style=\"color: #333333;\">Study in Italy<\/span><\/li>\n<li><span style=\"color: #333333;\">Masters\/PhD Degrees<\/span><\/li>\n<li><span style=\"color: #333333;\"><a style=\"color: #333333;\" href=\"https:\/\/studyinitaly.esteri.it\/en\/call-for-procedure\">Official Scholarship Website<\/a><\/span><\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<p><span style=\"color: #333333;\">The Ministry of Foreign Affairs and International Cooperation (MAECI) provides grants for the academic year 2023-2024 to foreign citizens who do not live in Italy and to Italian citizens living abroad (IRE).<\/span><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"color: #333333;\">These grants aim to promote cultural, scientific, and technological cooperation on an international level, support Italy&#8217;s economy on a global scale, and encourage the study of the Italian language and culture.<\/span><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"color: #333333;\">The grants are available for pursuing study, training, and research programs at Italian Higher Education Institutes, both public and legally recognized, following Law 288\/55 and its subsequent changes and additions.<\/span><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"color: #333333;\">If you want to apply for a Master&#8217;s Degree\/Higher Education in Arts, Music, and Dance (AFAM) Programmes\/Italian Language and Culture Advanced Courses, you must be of legal age.<\/span><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"color: #333333;\">You should be 28 years old by the deadline of this call (born after June 9th, 1994) unless it is a renewal for masters scholarships for international students.<\/span><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"color: #333333;\">Applicants must present a certificate demonstrating their Italian language proficiency to take an Italian-taught course.<\/span><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"color: #333333;\">The certificate should show a minimum level of B2 according to the Common European Framework of Reference for Languages (CEFR).<\/span><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"color: #333333;\">For those who wish to enroll in an English-taught course, a language certificate proving their proficiency in the English language is required.<\/span><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"color: #333333;\">The minimum level required is B2, according to the Common European Framework of Reference for Languages (CEFR).<\/span><\/p>\n<p>&nbsp;<\/p>\n<h2><span style=\"color: #333333;\">4. DAAD Helmut-Schmidt Masters Scholarships for Public Policy and Good Governance<\/span><\/h2>\n<ul>\n<li><span style=\"color: #333333;\">Study in Germany<\/span><\/li>\n<li><span style=\"color: #333333;\">Master\u2019s Degree<\/span><\/li>\n<li><span style=\"color: #333333;\"><a style=\"color: #333333;\" href=\"https:\/\/www.daad.de\/deutschland\/stipendium\/datenbank\/en\/21148-scholarship-database\/?status=&amp;origin=&amp;subjectGrps=&amp;daad=&amp;q=public%20policy&amp;page=1&amp;detail=50026397\">Official Scholarship Website<\/a><\/span><\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<p><span style=\"color: #333333;\">The Helmut-Schmidt-Programme Masters Scholarships for Public Policy and Good Governance Programme, offered by DAAD, provides exceptional graduates from developing countries with an opportunity to pursue a Master&#8217;s degree in fields that are crucial for the social, political, and economic growth of their home country.<\/span><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"color: #333333;\">These masters scholarships for international students are conducted at German higher education institutions.<\/span><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"color: #333333;\">First, they seek graduates from developing countries with a first university degree in social and political sciences, law, economics, public policy, and administration.<\/span><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"color: #333333;\">Ideal candidates should strongly desire to contribute to their home countries or regions&#8217; social, political, and economic development.<\/span><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"color: #333333;\">They also look for applicants who have gained practical experiences relevant to the program, such as professional experience, internships, or political and social commitments.<\/span><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"color: #333333;\">Additionally, each course has its selection criteria, such as degree, grades, language proficiency, and work experience, which must be met along with DAAD&#8217;s selection criteria.<\/span><\/p>\n<p><img decoding=\"async\" class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-1832\" src=\"https:\/\/abroadin.com\/blog\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/07\/top-view-piggy-bank-with-notebooks-diploma-1.jpg\" alt=\"masters scholarships for international students\" width=\"785\" height=\"568\" srcset=\"https:\/\/abroadin.com\/blog\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/07\/top-view-piggy-bank-with-notebooks-diploma-1.jpg 785w, https:\/\/abroadin.com\/blog\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/07\/top-view-piggy-bank-with-notebooks-diploma-1-300x217.jpg 300w, https:\/\/abroadin.com\/blog\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/07\/top-view-piggy-bank-with-notebooks-diploma-1-768x556.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 785px) 100vw, 785px\" \/><\/p>\n<h2><span style=\"color: #333333;\">5. The Glenmore Medical Postgraduate Scholarship at the University of Edinburgh<\/span><\/h2>\n<ul>\n<li><span style=\"color: #333333;\">Study in the UK<\/span><\/li>\n<li><span style=\"color: #333333;\">Master\u2019s Degree<\/span><\/li>\n<li><span style=\"color: #333333;\"><a style=\"color: #333333;\" href=\"http:\/\/www.ed.ac.uk\/schools-departments\/student-funding\/postgraduate\/international\/medicine-vet-medicine\/glenmore\">Official Scholarship Website<\/a><\/span><\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<p><span style=\"color: #333333;\">Three scholarships are available for postgraduate full-time one-year Masters\u2019 studies for eligible Human Medical programs the university offers in the 2023-2024 academic session.<\/span><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"color: #333333;\">The scholarships will be awarded to applicants accepted for admission in the 2023-2024 academic year to one of the above-listed eligible Human Medical programs.<\/span><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"color: #333333;\">To be eligible for masters scholarships for international students, applicants must have received an offer from the University of Edinburgh and have either accepted it or plan to do so.<\/span><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"color: #333333;\">Upon completing their studies, successful applicants are expected to use their enhanced medical education to benefit impoverished countries need countries.<\/span><\/p>\n<p>&nbsp;<\/p>\n<h2><span style=\"color: #333333;\">6. Schwarzman Scholars Program at Tsinghua University<\/span><\/h2>\n<ul>\n<li><span style=\"color: #333333;\">Study in China<\/span><\/li>\n<li><span style=\"color: #333333;\">Master\u2019s Degree<\/span><\/li>\n<li><span style=\"color: #333333;\"><a style=\"color: #333333;\" href=\"http:\/\/schwarzmanscholars.org\/\">Official Scholarship Website<\/a><\/span><\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<p><span style=\"color: #333333;\">Schwarzman Scholars is a scholarship program that aims to groom the next generation of world leaders in response to the 21st-century geopolitical landscape.<\/span><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"color: #333333;\">The program offers a one-year master&#8217;s degree at Tsinghua University in Beijing, known for its academic excellence.<\/span><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"color: #333333;\">It is open to the brightest and most talented students who wish to enhance their leadership skills and professional networks.<\/span><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"color: #333333;\">Candidates of these masters scholarships for international students must be at least 18 but must still be 29 as of August 1st of their Schwarzman Scholars enrollment year.<\/span><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"color: #333333;\">Suppose you are applying to be a Schwarzman Scholar and are currently enrolled in an undergraduate degree program.<\/span><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"color: #333333;\">In that case, ensuring that all degree requirements will be completed before August 1st of your enrollment year is essential.<\/span><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"color: #333333;\">There are no restrictions on the field of study. Still, applicants must explain how participating in the program will enhance their leadership potential within their chosen field, regardless of their major.<\/span><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"color: #333333;\">Applicants must have excellent English language skills to be eligible for teaching, as all instruction will be in English.<\/span><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"color: #333333;\">If English is not their native language, they must provide official test scores from an approved English proficiency exam.<\/span><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"color: #333333;\">Acceptable exams include the internet-based Test of English as a Foreign Language (TOEFL iBT) with a minimum score of 100.<\/span><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"color: #333333;\">If you went to a college or university where English was the language of instruction for at least two years, you do not need to meet this requirement.<\/span><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"color: #333333;\">Additionally, if you have a Master&#8217;s degree or higher and have studied English for at least two years, this requirement is also waived.<\/span><\/p>\n<p>&nbsp;<\/p>\n<h2><span style=\"color: #333333;\">7. UWE Chancellor\u2019s Scholarships for International Students<\/span><\/h2>\n<ul>\n<li><span style=\"color: #333333;\">Study in the UK<\/span><\/li>\n<li><span style=\"color: #333333;\">Master\u2019s Degree<\/span><\/li>\n<li><span style=\"color: #333333;\"><a style=\"color: #333333;\" href=\"https:\/\/www.uwe.ac.uk\/courses\/funding\/chancellors-scholarship\">Official Scholarship Website<\/a><\/span><\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<p><span style=\"color: #333333;\">The University of the West of England in Bristol provides international students with over \u00a3100,000 in scholarships yearly.<\/span><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"color: #333333;\">One such scholarship is the Chancellor&#8217;s Scholarship, which requires the recipient to intern at the International Development Office and other departments.<\/span><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"color: #333333;\">Additionally, the recipient of masters scholarships for international students will have to perform ambassadorial duties for the university during their studies.<\/span><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"color: #333333;\">To qualify for the scholarship, you must meet the following requirements:<\/span><\/p>\n<ul>\n<li><span style=\"color: #333333;\">Attain an undergraduate degree equivalent to a British 1<sup>st,<\/sup><\/span><\/li>\n<li><span style=\"color: #333333;\">Possess an unconditional offer or a conditional offer that only requires IELTS or an equivalent English language certification,<\/span><\/li>\n<li><span style=\"color: #333333;\">Be a first-time student at UWE Bristol with no prior UK education,<\/span><\/li>\n<li><span style=\"color: #333333;\">Be classified as an overseas student for fee purposes,<\/span><\/li>\n<li><span style=\"color: #333333;\">Not be sponsored or already awarded another scholarship,<\/span><\/li>\n<li><span style=\"color: #333333;\">Submit official transcripts during the application process.<\/span><\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<p>&nbsp;<\/p>\n<h2><span s